'''Allan Monteiro Dias''' (born 19 October 1988), known as '''Allan Dias''', is a Brazilian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[União Recreativa dos Trabalhadores|URT]] as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]].

==Club career==
Born in [[Rio de Janeiro]], Allan Dias graduated in [[São Paulo FC]]'s youth setup, appearing on the bench in a 2–0 home success against [[Figueirense Futebol Clube|Figueirense]] on 28 June 2007. However, after failing to make a first-team appearance for ''Tricolor'', he was subsequently loaned to [[Toledo Colônia Work]], [[Volta Redonda Futebol Clube|Volta Redonda]], [[Ituano Futebol Clube|Ituano]], [[Guaratinguetá Futebol|Guaratinguetá]] and [[Esporte Clube Santo André|Santo André]], respectively.

In April 2011 Allan Dias joined [[Associação Desportiva São Caetano|São Caetano]]. However, after being sparingly used at ''Azulão'', he moved to [[Red Bull Brasil]] on loan in February 2013; after scoring seven times in only 16 matches, Allan Dias joined Guaratinguetá.<ref>[http://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/guaratingueta/noticia/2013/05/guara-apresenta-meias-allan-dias-e-acleisson-e-fecha-elenco-para-serie-b.html Guará apresenta meias Allan Dias e Acleisson e fecha elenco para Série B (''Guará'' presents midfielders Allan Dias and Acleisson and closes roster for Série B)]; Globo Esporte, 23 May 2013 {{pt icon}}</ref>

On 10 January 2014 Allan Dias returned to Red Bull Brasil, this time in a permanent deal.<ref>[http://www.redbullbrasil.com.br/pt/news-detail_1064.html O bom filho a casa torna! Allan Dias retorna ao Red Bull Brasil para a disputa do Campeonato Paulista Série A2 (The good son returns home! Allan Dias returns to Red Bull Brasil for the dispute of Campeonato Paulista Série A2)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502132955/http://www.redbullbrasil.com.br/pt/news-detail_1064.html |date=2014-05-02 }}; Red Bull Brasil's official website, 10 January 2014 {{pt icon}}</ref> After achieving promotion with the club, he moved to [[Associação Portuguesa de Desportos|Portuguesa]] on 24 April.<ref>[http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/esportes,portuguesa-contrata-allan-dias-ex-red-bull-para-reforcar-meio-campo,1158240,0.htm Portuguesa contrata Allan Dias, ex-Red Bull, para reforçar meio-campo (Portuguesa signs Allan Dias, former Red Bull player, to bolster midfield)]; [[O Estado de S. Paulo]], 24 April 2014 {{pt icon}}</ref>

On 4 November Allan Dias rescinded with ''Lusa'',<ref>[http://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/portuguesa/noticia/2014/11/jocinei-e-allan-dias-acertam-rescisao-de-contrato-e-deixam-portuguesa.html Jocinei e Allan Dias acertam rescisão de contrato e deixam a Portuguesa (Jocinei and Allan Dias sign contract rescision and leave Portuguesa)]; Globo Esporte, 4 November 2014 {{pt icon}}</ref> and returned to RB Brasil eight days later.<ref>[http://www.redbullbrasil.com.br/campeonato-paulista-2015/eu-voltei-red-bull-brasil-confirma-allan-dias-como-primeiro-reforco-para-o-paulistao-2015.html Red Bull Brasil confirma Allan Dias como primeiro reforço para o Paulistão 2015 (Red Bull Brasil confirms Allan Dias as the first signing for ''Paulistão'' 2015)]; Red Bull Brasil's official website, 12 November 2014 {{pt icon}}</ref>

